South Africa to Tax Mauritian Investments, l’Express Reports

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-06-22T06:01:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/south-africa-to-tax-mauritian-investments-l-express-reports.html
South Africa  will charge a 10
percent tax on gains from investments in some property
developments in  Mauritius , l’Express reported, without saying
where it obtained the information.  The tax will be deducted at source and was imposed after
negotiations for an agreement on double-taxation avoidance
between the countries, the Port Louis-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net . 